      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/91/2",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ مَمْلُوكٌ أُعْتِقَ يَوْمَ عَرَفَةَ قَالَ «إِذَا أَدْرَكَ أَحَدَ اَلْمَوْقِفَيْنِ فَقَدْ أَدْرَكَ اَلْحَجَّ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2892 - It was narrated from Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdullah (as): \"A servant was freed on the Day of Arafah.\"\nImam (as) said: \"If he reaches one of the two stations (Arafah or Muzdalifah), then he has caught the Hajj.\""
        ]
      }
    },
